WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.458 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.458 --> 00:00:41.110 align:middle line:90%


00:00:41.110 --> 00:00:42.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Let me know when I'm ready.

00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:42.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep, we're ready.

00:00:42.950 --> 00:00:43.750 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:48.170 align:middle line:84%
When I went into psychiatry in
1950, fortunately not knowing

00:00:48.170 --> 00:00:50.060 align:middle line:84%
anything, but one
of the conditions

00:00:50.060 --> 00:00:52.765 align:middle line:84%
was as a part of my
offer for the job,

00:00:52.765 --> 00:00:54.140 align:middle line:84%
I would have to
learn psychiatry,

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:56.030 align:middle line:90%
which is fair enough.

00:00:56.030 --> 00:01:00.642 align:middle line:84%
1950, we had no treatment for
any of the major psychosis.

00:01:00.642 --> 00:01:02.600 align:middle line:84%
The only treatment was
to lock them up forever.

00:01:02.600 --> 00:01:06.160 align:middle line:90%


00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:08.425 align:middle line:90%
We had no treatment.

00:01:08.425 --> 00:01:12.385 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:12.385 --> 00:01:18.330 align:middle line:90%


00:01:18.330 --> 00:01:22.710 align:middle line:84%
>> We don't really understand at
a deeper level that we are what

00:01:22.710 --> 00:01:23.790 align:middle line:90%
we eat.

00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:26.270 align:middle line:10%
And I usually say to people,
you know, you look down

00:01:26.270 --> 00:01:27.900 align:middle line:10%
at your dinner plate.

00:01:27.900 --> 00:01:33.780 align:middle line:84%
And what you see doesn't appear
like the raw material for hair

00:01:33.780 --> 00:01:36.630 align:middle line:90%
or skin or teeth or nails.

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:38.370 align:middle line:90%
But that's exactly what it is.

00:01:38.370 --> 00:01:40.800 align:middle line:84%
We are just food
recycling machines.

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:43.530 align:middle line:84%
>> People don't take care
of themselves for one reason

00:01:43.530 --> 00:01:44.670 align:middle line:90%
or another.

00:01:44.670 --> 00:01:47.640 align:middle line:10%
And they come to
the doctor expecting

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:51.840 align:middle line:10%
to be kind of bailed out by
taking a medicine, a chemical,

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:54.240 align:middle line:10%
in order to treat the disease.

00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:57.060 align:middle line:10%
>> I mean, if we look
back at the last 30 years,

00:01:57.060 --> 00:02:00.600 align:middle line:10%
Homo sapiens is in a
really sorry state.

00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:03.260 align:middle line:84%
There is no question that
there has been an increase

00:02:03.260 --> 00:02:04.910 align:middle line:90%
in mental health problems.

00:02:04.910 --> 00:02:06.450 align:middle line:84%
And the World
Health Organization

00:02:06.450 --> 00:02:11.290 align:middle line:84%
say that mental health problems
have become the major area

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:12.090 align:middle line:90%
of health concern.

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:15.720 align:middle line:90%


00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:20.880 align:middle line:10%
>> Psychiatry is very much
dominated by the pharmaceutical

00:02:20.880 --> 00:02:23.770 align:middle line:10%
industry, especially
at this time.

00:02:23.770 --> 00:02:26.610 align:middle line:84%
In fact, almost all of
medicine is dominated

00:02:26.610 --> 00:02:29.820 align:middle line:90%
by pharmaceutical companies.

00:02:29.820 --> 00:02:34.800 align:middle line:84%
It has virtually no emphasis
on nutrition, on lifestyle,

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:37.900 align:middle line:90%
on any of those things.

00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:39.540 align:middle line:84%
Everything is
supposed to be solved

00:02:39.540 --> 00:02:42.551 align:middle line:84%
by the use of
psychotropic drugs.

00:02:42.551 --> 00:02:46.479 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:46.479 --> 00:02:51.880 align:middle line:90%


00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:55.990 align:middle line:10%
>> In 1950, we used to
lock them up forever.

00:02:55.990 --> 00:02:59.004 align:middle line:10%
In 2007, we lock them up
with their drugs forever.

00:02:59.004 --> 00:02:59.920 align:middle line:90%
There's no difference.

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:02.336 align:middle line:84%
They said they may be worse
off today because they're also

00:03:02.336 --> 00:03:03.185 align:middle line:90%
being destroyed.

00:03:03.185 --> 00:03:04.810 align:middle line:84%
Their body chemistry
is being destroyed

00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:07.660 align:middle line:84%
by the modern drugs, which
didn't happen nearly so much

00:03:07.660 --> 00:03:09.860 align:middle line:90%
with the old drugs.

00:03:09.860 --> 00:03:12.440 align:middle line:10%
>> And we'd see some of the
worse things were sleepless

00:03:12.440 --> 00:03:17.860 align:middle line:10%
nights, the visions of demons in
the bedroom window when I tried

00:03:17.860 --> 00:03:19.490 align:middle line:10%
to sleep.

00:03:19.490 --> 00:03:27.370 align:middle line:84%
Just awful, like nightmares
at their worst, as I remember,

00:03:27.370 --> 00:03:30.450 align:middle line:90%
the hopelessness.

00:03:30.450 --> 00:03:34.840 align:middle line:84%
I remember going through
libraries looking for answers

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:38.950 align:middle line:84%
to mental illness,
schizophrenia, madness,

00:03:38.950 --> 00:03:42.460 align:middle line:90%
insanity, manias of all kinds.

00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:44.230 align:middle line:90%
There were no answers.

00:03:44.230 --> 00:03:48.910 align:middle line:10%
>> So, I can sort of remember
my first session with Dr.

00:03:48.910 --> 00:03:52.550 align:middle line:90%
Hoffer was very straightforward.

00:03:52.550 --> 00:03:55.030 align:middle line:84%
He said, oh, you
have schizophrenia.

00:03:55.030 --> 00:03:58.670 align:middle line:90%
And I went, I do?

00:03:58.670 --> 00:04:02.140 align:middle line:84%
And I actually had a
name for what I had.

00:04:02.140 --> 00:04:05.000 align:middle line:84%
It was-- and he said,
do you hear voices?

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:06.440 align:middle line:90%
Well, yes, I do.

00:04:06.440 --> 00:04:09.164 align:middle line:84%
Nobody's ever asked
me that before.

00:04:09.164 --> 00:04:10.830 align:middle line:84%
I guess they were
just such a part of me

00:04:10.830 --> 00:04:13.670 align:middle line:84%
that I didn't realize
that I had voices

00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:17.339 align:middle line:90%
until Dr. Hoffer asked me that.

00:04:17.339 --> 00:04:19.720 align:middle line:84%
You know, are people
talking about you?

00:04:19.720 --> 00:04:23.520 align:middle line:84%
And well, yeah, I hear people
talking about me all the time.

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:25.630 align:middle line:90%
And it makes me really nervous.

00:04:25.630 --> 00:04:30.270 align:middle line:84%
And you know, just,
it's hard to deal with.

00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:33.010 align:middle line:90%


00:04:33.010 --> 00:04:35.850 align:middle line:84%
>> In the past 60 years,
psychiatry has made little

00:04:35.850 --> 00:04:39.280 align:middle line:84%
progress in the treatment
of mental illness.

00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:43.200 align:middle line:84%
Some might say no
progress at all.

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:45.630 align:middle line:84%
New pharmaceutical treatments
are not very different

00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:49.200 align:middle line:84%
from the chemical
straightjackets of yesteryear.

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:52.020 align:middle line:84%
What other treatments
are available?

00:04:52.020 --> 00:04:54.120 align:middle line:84%
Not much if you stick
to the mainstream.

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:56.920 align:middle line:90%


00:04:56.920 --> 00:05:01.780 align:middle line:84%
Can there be a better way
to help the mentally ill?

00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:04.210 align:middle line:84%
This story is about a
biochemical approach

00:05:04.210 --> 00:05:05.740 align:middle line:90%
to schizophrenia.

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:08.800 align:middle line:84%
But it applies to
every one of us.

00:05:08.800 --> 00:05:12.400 align:middle line:84%
Can it be that our thoughts,
moods, and behaviors depend

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:13.930 align:middle line:90%
upon what we've had to eat?

00:05:13.930 --> 00:05:18.780 align:middle line:90%


00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:21.090 align:middle line:84%
Abram Hoffer was born
a few miles south

00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:24.150 align:middle line:90%
of Weyburn, Saskatchewan.

00:05:24.150 --> 00:05:26.670 align:middle line:84%
His parents were Austrians
of Jewish descent

00:05:26.670 --> 00:05:31.490 align:middle line:84%
who had come to Canada
with agricultural vision.

00:05:31.490 --> 00:05:33.560 align:middle line:84%
By the time young
Abram came along,

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:37.670 align:middle line:84%
the Hoffer family farm
was doing very well.

00:05:37.670 --> 00:05:42.500 align:middle line:84%
Abram, however, preferred
school work to farmwork.

00:05:42.500 --> 00:05:45.077 align:middle line:84%
In school, Abrams studied
the pellagra epidemic.

00:05:45.077 --> 00:05:48.060 align:middle line:90%


00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Pellagra killed
100,000 Americans

00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:53.190 align:middle line:90%
before its cause was discovered.

00:05:53.190 --> 00:05:56.610 align:middle line:84%
It was caused by a deficiency
of niacin, also known

00:05:56.610 --> 00:05:57.460 align:middle line:90%
as vitamin B3.

00:05:57.460 --> 00:06:00.250 align:middle line:90%


00:06:00.250 --> 00:06:03.100 align:middle line:84%
The US government mandated
the enrichment of flour

00:06:03.100 --> 00:06:06.220 align:middle line:84%
with iron and B vitamins,
which ended the pellagra

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:09.820 align:middle line:90%
epidemic in 1938.

00:06:09.820 --> 00:06:11.710 align:middle line:84%
That was the same
year Abram Hoffer

00:06:11.710 --> 00:06:14.155 align:middle line:84%
got his Bachelor of Science
degree and turned 21.

00:06:14.155 --> 00:06:17.160 align:middle line:90%


00:06:17.160 --> 00:06:21.540 align:middle line:84%
He earned his PhD in
agricultural chemistry in 1944.

00:06:21.540 --> 00:06:25.300 align:middle line:84%
He became a medical
doctor in 1949.

00:06:25.300 --> 00:06:28.620 align:middle line:84%
Abram Hoffer was made head of
the psychiatric research branch

00:06:28.620 --> 00:06:33.770 align:middle line:84%
for the province of
Saskatchewan in 1950.

00:06:33.770 --> 00:06:36.716 align:middle line:84%
>> Psychiatry, by the way,
is what you might call--

00:06:36.716 --> 00:06:38.270 align:middle line:90%
it was a dumping ground.

00:06:38.270 --> 00:06:41.540 align:middle line:90%


00:06:41.540 --> 00:06:43.550 align:middle line:84%
Whenever a doctor ran
across a patient who

00:06:43.550 --> 00:06:48.830 align:middle line:84%
was either schizophrenic or
depressed or bipolar or senile,

00:06:48.830 --> 00:06:51.306 align:middle line:84%
they would then send
him on to psychiatry

00:06:51.306 --> 00:06:53.180 align:middle line:84%
who would then put him
into a mental hospital

00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:54.728 align:middle line:90%
or into an institution.

00:06:54.728 --> 00:06:59.499 align:middle line:90%


00:06:59.499 --> 00:07:01.290 align:middle line:84%
One of the main problems
in mental hospital

00:07:01.290 --> 00:07:02.790 align:middle line:84%
was that many of
these patients were

00:07:02.790 --> 00:07:04.900 align:middle line:90%
angry and excited and hostile.

00:07:04.900 --> 00:07:06.697 align:middle line:84%
The poor people were
terror stricken.

00:07:06.697 --> 00:07:07.530 align:middle line:90%
They were screaming.

00:07:07.530 --> 00:07:08.586 align:middle line:90%
They were shouting.

00:07:08.586 --> 00:07:09.800 align:middle line:90%
There was bedlam.

00:07:09.800 --> 00:07:12.180 align:middle line:84%
Bedlam was a good term for
any old mental hospital.

00:07:12.180 --> 00:07:14.580 align:middle line:90%
There was really bedlam there.

00:07:14.580 --> 00:07:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And the main thing was to get
people barbituates or sedatives

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:22.610 align:middle line:90%
to try and relax them a bit.

00:07:22.610 --> 00:07:26.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Anti-psychotic or neuroleptic
drugs were discovered

00:07:26.340 --> 00:07:28.650 align:middle line:90%
in the 1950s.

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:32.154 align:middle line:84%
Chlorpromazine was the
best known of these.

00:07:32.154 --> 00:07:34.620 align:middle line:84%
These drugs spread
like wildfire through

00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:36.316 align:middle line:90%
the psychiatric community.

00:07:36.316 --> 00:07:41.807 align:middle line:90%


00:07:41.807 --> 00:07:44.140 align:middle line:84%
>> And these drugs settled
them down very, very quickly.

00:07:44.140 --> 00:07:45.390 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing.

00:07:45.390 --> 00:07:47.910 align:middle line:84%
You could get a screaming,
shouting, crying patient.

00:07:47.910 --> 00:07:49.660 align:middle line:90%
And two days later, he's--

00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:51.770 align:middle line:90%
he's blah.

00:07:51.770 --> 00:07:53.742 align:middle line:90%
Now, he wasn't any better.

00:07:53.742 --> 00:07:54.950 align:middle line:90%
But he appeared to be better.

00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:56.887 align:middle line:90%
He was socially a lot better.

00:07:56.887 --> 00:07:57.720 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't think.

00:07:57.720 --> 00:07:58.510 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't reason.

00:07:58.510 --> 00:07:59.468 align:middle line:90%
They had no motivation.

00:07:59.468 --> 00:08:01.960 align:middle line:84%
They were slobbering sitting
in front of their TV.

00:08:01.960 --> 00:08:03.340 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't work.

00:08:03.340 --> 00:08:05.492 align:middle line:90%
They were hopelessly ill people.

00:08:05.492 --> 00:08:07.950 align:middle line:84%
And the only advantage was that
they weren't running around

00:08:07.950 --> 00:08:10.640 align:middle line:90%
in the streets crying.

00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:12.989 align:middle line:84%
They were being locked
up or kept at home,

00:08:12.989 --> 00:08:14.030 align:middle line:90%
and no one knew about it.

00:08:14.030 --> 00:08:16.720 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:19.900 align:middle line:84%
That was the situation
of psychiatry.

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:23.230 align:middle line:84%
So we were put in charge of
all the failure in medicine.

00:08:23.230 --> 00:08:27.206 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:27.206 --> 00:08:34.169 align:middle line:90%


00:08:34.169 --> 00:08:41.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Psychiatrists have become
a group that spend their time

00:08:41.830 --> 00:08:45.760 align:middle line:84%
looking at symptoms,
coming up with a label,

00:08:45.760 --> 00:08:47.290 align:middle line:90%
and prescribing a drug.

00:08:47.290 --> 00:08:50.020 align:middle line:84%
That's basically what
they do at this point.

00:08:50.020 --> 00:08:52.330 align:middle line:84%
It used to be-- when I
went through residency,

00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:54.670 align:middle line:84%
there was a lot of
emphasis on psychotherapy

00:08:54.670 --> 00:08:56.980 align:middle line:84%
and trying to help people
psychoanalytically,

00:08:56.980 --> 00:08:59.530 align:middle line:90%
or in psychotherapy.

00:08:59.530 --> 00:09:01.600 align:middle line:84%
But the point is that
psychiatrists really just

00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:02.800 align:middle line:90%
don't even do that anymore.

00:09:02.800 --> 00:09:07.600 align:middle line:84%
They basically are just
basically pill pushers

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:11.110 align:middle line:90%
for the pharmaceutical industry.

00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:13.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to me, it's
almost like a brainwashing

00:09:13.540 --> 00:09:17.500 align:middle line:84%
of the medical profession
that this is the only way

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:18.300 align:middle line:90%
to do things.

00:09:18.300 --> 00:09:20.930 align:middle line:90%


00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:26.930 align:middle line:84%
The pharmaceutical companies
support the medical schools

00:09:26.930 --> 00:09:27.920 align:middle line:90%
to a great extent.

00:09:27.920 --> 00:09:30.140 align:middle line:90%
They support the journals.

00:09:30.140 --> 00:09:37.790 align:middle line:84%
The first 50 pages of any
important medical journal

00:09:37.790 --> 00:09:41.810 align:middle line:84%
is taken up by advertisements
for various medications,

00:09:41.810 --> 00:09:42.680 align:middle line:90%
various drugs.

00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:48.390 align:middle line:90%


00:09:48.390 --> 00:09:51.690 align:middle line:10%
>> The large mental hospital at
Weyburn was one of the two main

00:09:51.690 --> 00:09:53.700 align:middle line:10%
mental hospitals
in the province,

00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:58.260 align:middle line:10%
and one of Hoffer's
chief responsibilities.

00:09:58.260 --> 00:10:01.290 align:middle line:84%
When it was built in 1920,
it was the largest building

00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:04.790 align:middle line:90%
in the commonwealth.

00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:09.470 align:middle line:84%
Over half the patients at
Weyburn were schizophrenic.

00:10:09.470 --> 00:10:14.080 align:middle line:10%
>> Dr. [INAUDIBLE],, who was
in charge of the whole unit,

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:17.750 align:middle line:10%
he was in charge of
psychiatric services branch.

00:10:17.750 --> 00:10:20.030 align:middle line:10%
He was a very kind man.

00:10:20.030 --> 00:10:24.650 align:middle line:84%
He also had the idea that
the Quakers had in 1850.

00:10:24.650 --> 00:10:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And this was that, first of
all, you had to provide shelter.

00:10:27.320 --> 00:10:29.420 align:middle line:84%
Second, you have to
provide good food.

00:10:29.420 --> 00:10:31.650 align:middle line:10%
Third, you had to be
kind and sympathetic.

00:10:31.650 --> 00:10:35.690 align:middle line:84%
The Quakers in 1850 didn't
believe in doctors or nurses.

00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:39.150 align:middle line:84%
They would take insane
people, up to 12,

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:41.960 align:middle line:84%
move them into a house
without nurses or doctors.

00:10:41.960 --> 00:10:43.489 align:middle line:90%
Their own people would run them.

00:10:43.489 --> 00:10:44.780 align:middle line:90%
And they would hold them there.

00:10:44.780 --> 00:10:46.370 align:middle line:90%
They'd be gentle to them, kind.

00:10:46.370 --> 00:10:47.570 align:middle line:90%
They'd work with them.

00:10:47.570 --> 00:10:49.820 align:middle line:84%
Every Saturday night, they'd
have a party and a dance.

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:52.220 align:middle line:84%
And the staff would
dance with the patients.

00:10:52.220 --> 00:10:54.680 align:middle line:84%
It was really a very
humane situation.

00:10:54.680 --> 00:10:58.390 align:middle line:90%


00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:03.580 align:middle line:10%
>> We had 2,000
seriously ill people,

00:11:03.580 --> 00:11:08.330 align:middle line:10%
who obviously were in need
of anything we could do.

00:11:08.330 --> 00:11:13.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Humphry Osmond was
born in England in 1917.

00:11:13.490 --> 00:11:16.460 align:middle line:84%
Osmond studied psychiatry
while acting as an army surgeon

00:11:16.460 --> 00:11:17.600 align:middle line:90%
during World War II.

00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:20.750 align:middle line:90%


00:11:20.750 --> 00:11:22.580 align:middle line:84%
Later, with John
Smythies, he had

00:11:22.580 --> 00:11:24.800 align:middle line:84%
done some of the earliest
scientific research

00:11:24.800 --> 00:11:25.640 align:middle line:90%
with mescaline.

00:11:25.640 --> 00:11:29.540 align:middle line:90%


00:11:29.540 --> 00:11:31.670 align:middle line:10%
They noted that its
chemical compound was

00:11:31.670 --> 00:11:34.400 align:middle line:10%
similar to adrenaline, and
that mescaline's effects

00:11:34.400 --> 00:11:37.145 align:middle line:10%
on perception were similar
to schizophrenic symptoms.

00:11:37.145 --> 00:11:40.860 align:middle line:90%


00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:42.990 align:middle line:84%
Osmond came to work
at the Weyburn Mental

00:11:42.990 --> 00:11:48.480 align:middle line:90%
Hospital in 1952.

00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:51.150 align:middle line:84%
He introduced Aldous
Huxley to mescaline,

00:11:51.150 --> 00:11:54.720 align:middle line:84%
participated in a native
Canadian peyote ceremony,

00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:56.760 align:middle line:84%
and coined the
term "psychedelic"

00:11:56.760 --> 00:11:59.410 align:middle line:90%
while living in Weyburn.

00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:03.390 align:middle line:84%
>> We didn't feel we wanted to
make a great deal of money out

00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:04.190 align:middle line:90%
of these things.

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:07.970 align:middle line:84%
We simply wanted to find things
that would help people not

00:12:07.970 --> 00:12:14.320 align:middle line:84%
get ill, which I, being rather
out of date and old-fashioned,

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:17.650 align:middle line:90%
I felt was a good thing to do.

00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:20.330 align:middle line:84%
>> We are able to hold
our world constant.

00:12:20.330 --> 00:12:22.660 align:middle line:84%
For the schizophrenic
person, this constancy

00:12:22.660 --> 00:12:25.690 align:middle line:84%
breaks down, or
begins to break down,

00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:30.470 align:middle line:84%
which is worse because
of the uncertainty.

00:12:30.470 --> 00:12:33.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Schizophrenia is
characterized by abnormalities

00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:34.955 align:middle line:90%
in the perception of reality.

00:12:34.955 --> 00:12:38.360 align:middle line:90%


00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:42.080 align:middle line:84%
Distortions in perception
may affect all the senses--

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:47.270 align:middle line:84%
sight, hearing, taste,
smell, and touch.

00:12:47.270 --> 00:12:51.770 align:middle line:84%
But it most commonly manifests
as hallucinations and delusions

00:12:51.770 --> 00:12:55.440 align:middle line:84%
or disorganized
speech and thinking.

00:12:55.440 --> 00:13:01.450 align:middle line:84%
>> You have a constant
noise, not always voices,

00:13:01.450 --> 00:13:03.290 align:middle line:90%
at least for me.

00:13:03.290 --> 00:13:04.370 align:middle line:90%
It was just noise.

00:13:04.370 --> 00:13:10.190 align:middle line:84%
It was just like every
noise is amplified.

00:13:10.190 --> 00:13:13.250 align:middle line:90%
And so you just want quiet.

00:13:13.250 --> 00:13:14.390 align:middle line:90%
You just want peace.

00:13:14.390 --> 00:13:17.270 align:middle line:90%
You just want to make it stop.

00:13:17.270 --> 00:13:20.090 align:middle line:84%
And there's no way
of making it stop.

00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:24.590 align:middle line:84%
You have voices telling you,
you know, you're just so stupid.

00:13:24.590 --> 00:13:26.330 align:middle line:90%
And you're just lousy.

00:13:26.330 --> 00:13:27.740 align:middle line:90%
And you don't deserve to live.

00:13:27.740 --> 00:13:31.250 align:middle line:84%
And you should just go
jump off that bridge.

00:13:31.250 --> 00:13:33.320 align:middle line:84%
Or why don't you
slit your wrists?

00:13:33.320 --> 00:13:34.260 align:middle line:90%
Or why don't you--

00:13:34.260 --> 00:13:36.620 align:middle line:84%
you know, you're
such a bad person.

00:13:36.620 --> 00:13:40.400 align:middle line:84%
Just this all negative,
negative, negative constantly

00:13:40.400 --> 00:13:41.930 align:middle line:90%
on you.

00:13:41.930 --> 00:13:45.320 align:middle line:84%
>> And Dr. Hoffer and Osmond
originally hypothesized that

00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:48.230 align:middle line:84%
there was a substance
that was capable--

00:13:48.230 --> 00:13:51.170 align:middle line:84%
that was found in
schizophrenics that

00:13:51.170 --> 00:13:54.890 align:middle line:84%
could distort reality
and affect their brain.

00:13:54.890 --> 00:13:59.390 align:middle line:84%
And they then isolated
something called adrenochrome.

00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:05.270 align:middle line:84%
They found that the
adrenochrome could actually

00:14:05.270 --> 00:14:08.510 align:middle line:84%
produce schizophrenic
symptoms, could cause

00:14:08.510 --> 00:14:10.830 align:middle line:84%
hallucinations,
delusions, and so on.

00:14:10.830 --> 00:14:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And adrenochrome is an
oxidized product of adrenaline.

00:14:16.490 --> 00:14:19.910 align:middle line:84%
And adrenaline often occurs
when you're under stress.

00:14:19.910 --> 00:14:24.410 align:middle line:84%
And people who have
the genetics for it

00:14:24.410 --> 00:14:28.250 align:middle line:84%
can then develop
these oxidized stress

00:14:28.250 --> 00:14:33.050 align:middle line:84%
hormones that are then capable
of actually poisoning a person.

00:14:33.050 --> 00:14:35.540 align:middle line:84%
>> If you had the right genes,
if you had the right genetic

00:14:35.540 --> 00:14:39.290 align:middle line:84%
structure-- now there's
evidence for that--

00:14:39.290 --> 00:14:42.260 align:middle line:84%
which would allow the
conversion of too much

00:14:42.260 --> 00:14:43.640 align:middle line:84%
adrenaline to
adrenochrome, which

00:14:43.640 --> 00:14:48.260 align:middle line:84%
was a hallucinogen in the
brain, that if this happened,

00:14:48.260 --> 00:14:51.470 align:middle line:84%
that this would act on the
brain as if they had taken LSD.

00:14:51.470 --> 00:14:53.120 align:middle line:84%
And they would then
become psychotic.

00:14:53.120 --> 00:15:00.270 align:middle line:84%
>> With adrenochrome, your
legs seem a very long way down.

00:15:00.270 --> 00:15:03.980 align:middle line:84%
Your clothes may
become uncomfortable.

00:15:03.980 --> 00:15:05.810 align:middle line:84%
And particularly,
if you are convinced

00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:10.760 align:middle line:84%
that something is wrong,
almost intolerable.

00:15:10.760 --> 00:15:15.020 align:middle line:84%
Small distortions can
be even more frightening

00:15:15.020 --> 00:15:17.300 align:middle line:84%
than large ones because
you can't be sure

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:19.250 align:middle line:90%
that they are distortions.

00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:23.257 align:middle line:84%
And as tension mounts, so
does one's uncertainty.

00:15:23.257 --> 00:15:26.120 align:middle line:90%


00:15:26.120 --> 00:15:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Ours is a simple,
comprehensive hypothesis that

00:15:29.780 --> 00:15:32.120 align:middle line:90%
wasn't based upon chance.

00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:34.700 align:middle line:84%
We actually derived
our hypothesis

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.560 align:middle line:84%
from very careful
observation that

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:39.710 align:middle line:84%
would be made by Humphry Osmond
and John Smythies and myself.

00:15:39.710 --> 00:15:41.000 align:middle line:90%
That was our hypothesis.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:43.829 align:middle line:84%
Ours is the only rational
hypothesis there is.

00:15:43.829 --> 00:15:46.120 align:middle line:84%
The average psychiatrist will
not answer your question.

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:47.536 align:middle line:84%
Ask him what causes
schizophrenia,

00:15:47.536 --> 00:15:48.804 align:middle line:90%
he says, I don't know.

00:15:48.804 --> 00:15:49.970 align:middle line:90%
They think it's biochemical.

00:15:49.970 --> 00:15:51.350 align:middle line:90%
They use the word biochemical.

00:15:51.350 --> 00:15:53.395 align:middle line:84%
But they don't understand
what that means.

00:15:53.395 --> 00:15:55.520 align:middle line:84%
Because when you load
someone up with a toxic drug,

00:15:55.520 --> 00:15:57.436 align:middle line:84%
you're not giving him a
biochemical treatment.

00:15:57.436 --> 00:15:58.970 align:middle line:90%
You are merely poisoning him.

00:15:58.970 --> 00:16:00.740 align:middle line:84%
And it's easy enough
to poison people.

00:16:00.740 --> 00:16:03.176 align:middle line:90%
That's no problem.

00:16:03.176 --> 00:16:05.550 align:middle line:84%
So there are no theories that
are acceptable except ours.

00:16:05.550 --> 00:16:11.810 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.810 --> 00:16:13.550 align:middle line:84%
>> To offset the
effects of adrenochrome,

00:16:13.550 --> 00:16:17.270 align:middle line:84%
we turn to the cheapest, safest,
and most easily available

00:16:17.270 --> 00:16:18.670 align:middle line:90%
substance--

00:16:18.670 --> 00:16:20.360 align:middle line:90%
niacin, vitamin B.

00:16:20.360 --> 00:16:25.280 align:middle line:84%
>> We by that time knew that
niacin might protect the cell

00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:27.710 align:middle line:84%
against the effect
of adrenochrome.

00:16:27.710 --> 00:16:30.320 align:middle line:84%
So I decided that
we would try niacin.

00:16:30.320 --> 00:16:35.680 align:middle line:90%


00:16:35.680 --> 00:16:39.580 align:middle line:84%
>> It's 37 years
since I was ill.

00:16:39.580 --> 00:16:41.830 align:middle line:90%
I have recovered completely.

00:16:41.830 --> 00:16:44.230 align:middle line:84%
I always think of my
recovery as taking place

00:16:44.230 --> 00:16:49.370 align:middle line:84%
in about three weeks,
or 19 days to be exact.

00:16:49.370 --> 00:16:53.020 align:middle line:84%
The theory that Dr. Hoffer
has that the adrenals produce

00:16:53.020 --> 00:16:55.840 align:middle line:84%
this toxic
adrenalutin and that's

00:16:55.840 --> 00:17:00.740 align:middle line:84%
like LSD in the body,
that fits my story.

00:17:00.740 --> 00:17:05.920 align:middle line:84%
And I think my own part in
it was overdosing on sugar.

00:17:05.920 --> 00:17:09.040 align:middle line:10%
I love my sweets.

00:17:09.040 --> 00:17:10.000 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't aware.

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:15.986 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really know that
sugar can affect my mind.

00:17:15.986 --> 00:17:18.069 align:middle line:84%
And he said, we'll put you
on the niacin and watch

00:17:18.069 --> 00:17:19.900 align:middle line:90%
what happens.

00:17:19.900 --> 00:17:23.260 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't have
any expectations.

00:17:23.260 --> 00:17:25.460 align:middle line:90%
But something happened.

00:17:25.460 --> 00:17:29.720 align:middle line:84%
I make recommendations for
vitamins or supplements

00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:34.240 align:middle line:84%
always in terms of
cleansing and building.

00:17:34.240 --> 00:17:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And I make
recommendations for diet.

00:17:36.200 --> 00:17:41.927 align:middle line:90%


00:17:41.927 --> 00:17:44.510 align:middle line:84%
>> It became mandatory for all
my patients that they would all

00:17:44.510 --> 00:17:45.470 align:middle line:90%
go onto niacin.

00:17:45.470 --> 00:17:47.280 align:middle line:90%
I used drugs too.

00:17:47.280 --> 00:17:49.940 align:middle line:84%
The vitamin didn't work fast
enough, and the drugs did.

00:17:49.940 --> 00:17:53.900 align:middle line:84%
So, the best solution
was to combine them.

00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:56.500 align:middle line:84%
So I'd start my patients
on the drugs, which

00:17:56.500 --> 00:17:58.380 align:middle line:84%
would help settle it
down very quickly,

00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:00.820 align:middle line:84%
help take away their
anxiety, their hostility,

00:18:00.820 --> 00:18:01.762 align:middle line:90%
their depression.

00:18:01.762 --> 00:18:02.720 align:middle line:90%
Start them on vitamins.

00:18:02.720 --> 00:18:06.710 align:middle line:90%


00:18:06.710 --> 00:18:08.750 align:middle line:84%
And we used the drugs as
you would use a crutch

00:18:08.750 --> 00:18:10.327 align:middle line:90%
for a person with a broken leg.

00:18:10.327 --> 00:18:12.660 align:middle line:84%
As soon as the leg is mended,
you throw away the crutch.

00:18:12.660 --> 00:18:14.420 align:middle line:84%
As soon as our
patients are mended,

00:18:14.420 --> 00:18:16.020 align:middle line:90%
we throw away the drugs.

00:18:16.020 --> 00:18:18.027 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's how
they ought to be used.

00:18:18.027 --> 00:18:19.610 align:middle line:84%
So, that's where we
get the recoveries

00:18:19.610 --> 00:18:21.660 align:middle line:90%
that we see by the combination.

00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:24.380 align:middle line:84%
This is what's called
orthomolecular.

00:18:24.380 --> 00:18:28.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Two-time Nobel Prize-winning
chemist Linus Pauling also

00:18:28.130 --> 00:18:32.260 align:middle line:84%
championed the use of
vitamins as treatment.

00:18:32.260 --> 00:18:35.410 align:middle line:84%
Pauling coined the term
"orthomolecular medicine"

00:18:35.410 --> 00:18:38.590 align:middle line:90%
in 1968.

00:18:38.590 --> 00:18:41.320 align:middle line:90%
The Greek "ortho" means correct.

00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:44.496 align:middle line:84%
So orthomolecular means
the right molecules

00:18:44.496 --> 00:18:45.370 align:middle line:90%
in the right amounts.

00:18:45.370 --> 00:18:48.150 align:middle line:90%


00:18:48.150 --> 00:18:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>> The medical profession
has been very hostile toward

00:18:51.100 --> 00:18:53.950 align:middle line:84%
orthomolecular medicine,
especially the psychiatric

00:18:53.950 --> 00:18:56.700 align:middle line:90%
profession.

00:18:56.700 --> 00:18:59.080 align:middle line:10%
I wasn't even aware
of it, of course,

00:18:59.080 --> 00:19:03.330 align:middle line:10%
until 1968 when Linus Pauling
published his very famous paper

00:19:03.330 --> 00:19:06.165 align:middle line:10%
in "Science" called
"Orthomolecular Psychiatry."

00:19:06.165 --> 00:19:10.880 align:middle line:84%
Pauling never accepted anyone's
word; he did his own thinking.

00:19:10.880 --> 00:19:13.860 align:middle line:84%
You know, Pauling was the
world's most famous scientist.

00:19:13.860 --> 00:19:18.070 align:middle line:84%
He had a double Nobel Prize,
one for his work with chemistry.

00:19:18.070 --> 00:19:21.450 align:middle line:84%
In fact, his work in chemistry
is the absolute basis

00:19:21.450 --> 00:19:22.560 align:middle line:90%
of all modern medicine.

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:26.670 align:middle line:84%
He showed how molecules
react with each other.

00:19:26.670 --> 00:19:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>> They started using nutrients
to help people's heads,

00:19:29.940 --> 00:19:32.502 align:middle line:90%
feed your heads.

00:19:32.502 --> 00:19:33.960 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold,
their whole body

00:19:33.960 --> 00:19:37.710 align:middle line:84%
got better because nutrients
don't just feed the head.

00:19:37.710 --> 00:19:39.810 align:middle line:90%
Nutrients feed the whole body.

00:19:39.810 --> 00:19:42.390 align:middle line:84%
And when you feed the body,
and the body gets healthier,

00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:43.990 align:middle line:90%
that feeds relationships.

00:19:43.990 --> 00:19:46.510 align:middle line:84%
And if you feed relationships,
then societies and cultures

00:19:46.510 --> 00:19:47.310 align:middle line:90%
improve.

00:19:47.310 --> 00:19:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And when they improve,
nations stop warring.

00:19:50.580 --> 00:19:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And when nations stop
warring, then you

00:19:52.350 --> 00:19:55.590 align:middle line:84%
can start taking care
of the planet again.

00:19:55.590 --> 00:19:59.040 align:middle line:84%
And so all of this
begins with nutrition.

00:19:59.040 --> 00:20:02.220 align:middle line:84%
>> It was literally only 200
generations ago we were all

00:20:02.220 --> 00:20:04.200 align:middle line:90%
hunters and gatherers.

00:20:04.200 --> 00:20:06.690 align:middle line:84%
We had no choice but to
eat everything organic.

00:20:06.690 --> 00:20:08.260 align:middle line:90%
Everything was whole.

00:20:08.260 --> 00:20:11.460 align:middle line:84%
And we would eat seeds
and fruits and vegetables.

00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:14.360 align:middle line:84%
All the animals we
ate were wild animals.

00:20:14.360 --> 00:20:18.360 align:middle line:84%
Wild animal has maybe 5%
of its body weight is fat.

00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:20.970 align:middle line:84%
Most of the animals we eat
today, even organic animals,

00:20:20.970 --> 00:20:23.950 align:middle line:90%
you're looking at 20%.

00:20:23.950 --> 00:20:27.475 align:middle line:84%
So, food has
phenomenally changed.

00:20:27.475 --> 00:20:31.440 align:middle line:84%
And now that we know how our
biology works in relation

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:37.290 align:middle line:84%
to food, it would be surprising
if we hadn't changed how

00:20:37.290 --> 00:20:39.780 align:middle line:84%
we think, how we
feel, and our pattern

00:20:39.780 --> 00:20:44.400 align:middle line:84%
of diseases, which clearly
are escalating out of control.

00:20:44.400 --> 00:20:47.760 align:middle line:84%
>> The brain is very
particularly dependent

00:20:47.760 --> 00:20:54.090 align:middle line:84%
on nutrition because this
organ is two pounds in weight.

00:20:54.090 --> 00:20:58.890 align:middle line:84%
And yet it consumes 20% of
circulating oxygen, glucose,

00:20:58.890 --> 00:21:00.750 align:middle line:90%
and other nutrients.

00:21:00.750 --> 00:21:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And so if you like, I describe
the brain as a nutrient hog.

00:21:05.550 --> 00:21:08.910 align:middle line:90%
It's using up 10 times more.

00:21:08.910 --> 00:21:11.730 align:middle line:84%
It's 10 times more
metabolically active.

00:21:11.730 --> 00:21:14.370 align:middle line:84%
So where there's a
shortfall in diet,

00:21:14.370 --> 00:21:18.880 align:middle line:84%
and where that plate
contains stripped down,

00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:21.630 align:middle line:84%
ersatz food, then
of course, the brain

00:21:21.630 --> 00:21:24.450 align:middle line:84%
is going to be one of the
first places that's affected.

00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:28.710 align:middle line:84%
And now we can see from studies
those particularly depriving

00:21:28.710 --> 00:21:31.710 align:middle line:84%
the developing brain
in utero of nutrients

00:21:31.710 --> 00:21:35.470 align:middle line:84%
is leading to lifelong
health problems--

00:21:35.470 --> 00:21:37.330 align:middle line:84%
mental health and
physical health.

00:21:37.330 --> 00:21:42.830 align:middle line:90%


00:21:42.830 --> 00:21:48.200 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the problems is
the scale of food processing.

00:21:48.200 --> 00:21:52.580 align:middle line:10%
And many people think in
terms of grains and sugars

00:21:52.580 --> 00:21:56.810 align:middle line:10%
and how they have
been processed.

00:21:56.810 --> 00:21:59.990 align:middle line:84%
There's an interesting
historical element here

00:21:59.990 --> 00:22:06.110 align:middle line:84%
in that the ancient Romans knew
more about grain processing

00:22:06.110 --> 00:22:12.320 align:middle line:84%
than people did up until the
early part of the 20th century.

00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:17.780 align:middle line:84%
That knowledge had been lost
for almost two millennia.

00:22:17.780 --> 00:22:20.600 align:middle line:84%
We've caught up,
and we've probably

00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:24.560 align:middle line:84%
superseded what
the Romans had done

00:22:24.560 --> 00:22:28.280 align:middle line:84%
in terms of not just
refining grains, refining

00:22:28.280 --> 00:22:33.270 align:middle line:84%
sugars, refining and creating
all sorts of artificial fats.

00:22:33.270 --> 00:22:36.330 align:middle line:90%


00:22:36.330 --> 00:22:40.500 align:middle line:84%
And most people, unless they
are very mindful of what

00:22:40.500 --> 00:22:43.620 align:middle line:84%
they are eating,
are basically eating

00:22:43.620 --> 00:22:46.650 align:middle line:90%
in this sea of junk food.

00:22:46.650 --> 00:22:49.740 align:middle line:84%
The solution is
really very simple.

00:22:49.740 --> 00:22:54.600 align:middle line:84%
And I can't claim
credit for the idea.

00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:58.980 align:middle line:84%
But it's basically going
back to fresh foods,

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:01.680 align:middle line:84%
avoiding almost
anything that comes

00:23:01.680 --> 00:23:06.165 align:middle line:90%
in a bottle, jar, can, or box.

00:23:06.165 --> 00:23:09.850 align:middle line:90%


00:23:09.850 --> 00:23:15.250 align:middle line:84%
>> These processed foods bring
about inflammatory conditions.

00:23:15.250 --> 00:23:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And these inflammatory
conditions

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:21.270 align:middle line:84%
are associated with
all of the problems

00:23:21.270 --> 00:23:24.510 align:middle line:84%
that we have today, including
psychiatric conditions,

00:23:24.510 --> 00:23:28.060 align:middle line:84%
neurological conditions,
cancer, diabetes,

00:23:28.060 --> 00:23:29.345 align:middle line:90%
heart disease, and so on.

