00:24:06.170 --> 00:24:09.300 align:middle line:90%
And so that's part of it.

00:24:09.300 --> 00:24:14.190 align:middle line:84%
There's also a kind of
orthodoxy or a belief

00:24:14.190 --> 00:24:18.650 align:middle line:84%
in the medical school
training that anything

00:24:18.650 --> 00:24:20.720 align:middle line:84%
that has to do with
nutrition is always

00:24:20.720 --> 00:24:23.190 align:middle line:90%
going to border on quackery.

00:24:23.190 --> 00:24:26.240 align:middle line:84%
Matter of fact, I was
told in medical school

00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:29.420 align:middle line:84%
any doctor that prescribes
a vitamin by definition

00:24:29.420 --> 00:24:32.030 align:middle line:90%
is a quack.

00:24:32.030 --> 00:24:36.380 align:middle line:84%
>> One other thing I'd like to
underline is that when we go

00:24:36.380 --> 00:24:42.140 align:middle line:84%
through medical school,
the first two years,

00:24:42.140 --> 00:24:44.900 align:middle line:84%
or the first year, we
learn a lot about anatomy

00:24:44.900 --> 00:24:47.330 align:middle line:90%
and physiology and biochemistry.

00:24:47.330 --> 00:24:50.600 align:middle line:84%
And then starting in the second
year, we get to pharmacology.

00:24:50.600 --> 00:24:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is that the
attitude in medical school

00:24:54.800 --> 00:24:58.390 align:middle line:84%
is that the physiology
and biochemistry,

00:24:58.390 --> 00:24:59.880 align:middle line:90%
well, that's kind of--

00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:01.080 align:middle line:90%
we have to know that.

00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:03.890 align:middle line:84%
But the real medicine
is pharmacology.

00:25:03.890 --> 00:25:07.070 align:middle line:84%
And that is the
orientation of physicians.

00:25:07.070 --> 00:25:09.860 align:middle line:84%
And what we are doing
in orthomolecular

00:25:09.860 --> 00:25:12.650 align:middle line:84%
psychiatry and orthomolecular
medicine is we're

00:25:12.650 --> 00:25:17.450 align:middle line:84%
going back to physiology
and biochemistry rather than

00:25:17.450 --> 00:25:18.410 align:middle line:90%
pharmacology.

00:25:18.410 --> 00:25:22.280 align:middle line:84%
We assume that the body has
the ability to heal itself

00:25:22.280 --> 00:25:23.930 align:middle line:90%
if given half a chance.

00:25:23.930 --> 00:25:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And the way that happens
is by supplying the body

00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:29.840 align:middle line:84%
with what it needs
and trying to remove

00:25:29.840 --> 00:25:33.680 align:middle line:90%
things that are toxic to it.

