00:30:49.836 --> 00:31:21.620 align:middle line:90%


00:31:21.620 --> 00:31:23.160 align:middle line:84%
The idea of the
Saskatchewan plan

00:31:23.160 --> 00:31:26.550 align:middle line:84%
was to build hospitals that
would be really good hospitals,

00:31:26.550 --> 00:31:29.640 align:middle line:84%
where people would be
held until they got well.

00:31:29.640 --> 00:31:31.980 align:middle line:84%
They would keep patients
even three to six, 12 months

00:31:31.980 --> 00:31:34.120 align:middle line:90%
if necessary.

00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.270 align:middle line:90%
Then the drugs came along.

00:31:36.270 --> 00:31:37.980 align:middle line:84%
They were so dramatic
that psychiatry

00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:42.000 align:middle line:84%
began to think we don't
need these hospitals.

00:31:42.000 --> 00:31:43.557 align:middle line:84%
Their plan was not
to really build

00:31:43.557 --> 00:31:45.390 align:middle line:84%
a large number of smaller
institutions where

00:31:45.390 --> 00:31:47.314 align:middle line:90%
they could house them properly.

00:31:47.314 --> 00:31:49.230 align:middle line:84%
Their plan was simply
to put them all on drugs

00:31:49.230 --> 00:31:50.840 align:middle line:90%
and discharge them.

00:31:50.840 --> 00:31:53.442 align:middle line:84%
And for a while, there was an
enormous feather in your cap

00:31:53.442 --> 00:31:54.900 align:middle line:84%
if the superintendent
of a hospital

00:31:54.900 --> 00:31:57.390 align:middle line:84%
could claim that he was
empty in his hospital

00:31:57.390 --> 00:31:58.944 align:middle line:90%
faster than you were.

00:31:58.944 --> 00:32:01.110 align:middle line:84%
If you started off the
