00:32:33.190 --> 00:32:35.770 align:middle line:90%
They have a lot of side effects.

00:32:35.770 --> 00:32:37.020 align:middle line:90%
So they go off them.

00:32:37.020 --> 00:32:40.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Basically, what we're dealing
with is a culture of life

00:32:40.260 --> 00:32:41.670 align:middle line:90%
and a culture of death.

00:32:41.670 --> 00:32:44.880 align:middle line:84%
And a culture of life
is to try to supply

00:32:44.880 --> 00:32:49.770 align:middle line:84%
the body with what it needs
and to keep away toxic things.

00:32:49.770 --> 00:32:53.490 align:middle line:84%
I think the culture of life
is an orthomolecular approach.

00:32:53.490 --> 00:32:57.420 align:middle line:84%
The culture of death is one
that focuses on profits.

00:32:57.420 --> 00:32:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
motivates everything.

00:32:59.550 --> 00:33:02.070 align:middle line:84%
So it's the financial
situation that

00:33:02.070 --> 00:33:04.830 align:middle line:84%
is motivating the
development of the drugs

00:33:04.830 --> 00:33:09.420 align:middle line:84%
and the paying dividends
to the stockholders

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:10.350 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:33:10.350 --> 00:33:11.710 align:middle line:90%
That's what's important.

00:33:11.710 --> 00:33:15.140 align:middle line:90%
That's what drives things.

00:33:15.140 --> 00:33:18.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Of course, this is
the future of medicine.

00:33:18.140 --> 00:33:19.150 align:middle line:90%
It works.

00:33:19.150 --> 00:33:20.610 align:middle line:90%
Number one, it works.

00:33:20.610 --> 00:33:22.610 align:middle line:90%
Number two, it's safe.

00:33:22.610 --> 00:33:25.440 align:middle line:90%
So why aren't we all doing this?

00:33:25.440 --> 00:33:29.150 align:middle line:84%
And I think the bottom
line is it is money.

00:33:29.150 --> 00:33:32.000 align:middle line:84%
The pharmaceutical industry
have such a tight hold

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:34.700 align:middle line:90%
on medical training.

00:33:34.700 --> 00:33:36.800 align:middle line:84%
So, the average
doctor just simply

00:33:36.800 --> 00:33:38.460 align:middle line:90%
doesn't learn this stuff.

00:33:38.460 --> 00:33:41.660 align:middle line:84%
And by the time they come
out of medical school,

00:33:41.660 --> 00:33:44.810 align:middle line:84%
they've got all this knowledge
about how to diagnose diseases

00:33:44.810 --> 00:33:47.570 align:middle line:84%
and which drugs
to use and so on.

00:33:47.570 --> 00:33:53.660 align:middle line:84%
And they've often been taught
that particular nutrients just

00:33:53.660 --> 00:33:55.020 align:middle line:90%
aren't effective.

00:33:55.020 --> 00:33:57.620 align:middle line:84%
You know, sort of
drug versus nutrient.

00:33:57.620 --> 00:33:59.060 align:middle line:84%
But of course,
this whole approach

00:33:59.060 --> 00:34:03.740 align:middle line:84%
is not about a different
kind of pill for an ill.

00:34:03.740 --> 00:34:06.922 align:middle line:84%
It's actually an entirely
different approach.

00:34:06.922 --> 00:34:09.380 align:middle line:84%
And then when you couple that
